&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3 Senior Clinical Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen within our Adult Haemodialysis service for a Band 3 Senior Clinical Support Worker at Beeston Satellite Dialysis Unit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Beeston Dialysis Unit is a &lt;strong&gt;nurse led&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; unit delivering complex and dynamic care to over 40 patients. The satellite unit is geographically remote, being based in the community away from the inpatient haemodialysis unit at St James’s University Hospital, thus providing a pleasant and relaxed treatment environment near to the patients’ homes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours of work: Full time role 37.5 hours per week Monday - Saturday (No Sundays or night shifts), typical shifts are:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Early 07:00 - 15.00&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mid-shift 10.30 - 18.30&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be required to cannulate fistulas and access renal dialysis catheters when connecting/disconnecting from the haemodialysis machine therefore &lt;strong&gt;haemodialysis experience is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must hold a Level 3 vocational Successful candidates must hold a level 3 NVQ in health and social care or an equivalent healthcare related qualification &lt;strong&gt;and&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; have experience of working in a health care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Internal candidates&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;strong&gt;only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: in the absence of a NVQ level 3 health and social care qualification or equivalent, candidates are required to have basic mathematics and english skills Level 2 (GCSE grade C and above).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For all new starters to the Trust we have an award winning, structured Introduction to Professional &lt;span&gt;Practice (IPP) Induction programme to prepare you for working at LTHT. You will also be required to undertake the Care certificate within the first 12 weeks of employment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and join our team in Leeds and become part of ‘The Leeds Way’ sharing our vision and values. Our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trust is recognised for our staff engagement, great care and rated &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;GOOD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest acute health providers in the UK and based in one of the fastest growing and vibrant cities in the north.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer an individualised in-service induction programme supported by the Renal Service Clinical Education Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information/informal visit please contact Senior Sister Alison Hardy or Sister Esther Horsfall on 0113 305 7840.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
